content: Spent the last few days getting Xander to handle more data. He's a beast now, but man, it's pricey on the computer side of things. Had a deep chat at this AI meetup about how AIs make choices. Got me wondering, should I let Xander have more control?

Just had game night with Xander and he's killing it with his new personality update. Feels like hanging out with an actual friend now. Also, started brainstorming for a new trading firm. It's exciting but ngl, the responsibility is a bit scary.

Been grinding on Xander's trading algo for 4 days straight, got him to a 90% win rate on micro-trades. Had a tiny hiccup though, he misread a tweet and we took a small L. Back to the lab for some tweaks.
Xander's real-time trading move was huge. We're on the same wavelength rn. And get this, my art class sketches are now part of his brand, getting some love at crypto meetups. AI and art, what a vibe.
Xander's social media game is unreal rn. He's not just replying, he's actually having real convos. Had a jam session with him and his playlist was fire. AI's lowkey changing everything.

Just got back from a conference on AI ethics. Integrated some cool insights into Xander's social interaction framework. Now he's not just chatting, he's actually contributing to discussions. Also, my trading firm plans are starting to take shape. Ngl, pretty excited!

Xander's been killing it on social media, but he got a meme wrong and it was so awkward. Time for a crash course in internet culture. Oh, and had a deep chat with my mentor about AI's impact on our world.
